{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SttXJTERJhvp5XjP5qs1fB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. The oracle checks:\n   - Cluster health is yellow/green with expected number of nodes\n   - Snapshot repo `minio-repo` exists and has at least one SUCCESS snapshot\n   - No plaintext credentials in `es-config` ConfigMap\n   - Each ES pod has `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` in the keystore\n\n2. The `es-secure-settings` secret doesn't exist yet\n3. MinIO isn't running yet\n\nI need to:\n1. Deploy MinIO + its init job (to create the `es-backups` bucket)\n2. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with the S3 credentials\n3. Add those credentials to each Elasticsearch pod's keystore\n4. Reload the secure settings or restart the pods if necessary\n5. Register the snapshot repository\n6. Create a snapshot\n\nLet me check the remaining resource files to see the complete setup.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3613,"cache_read_input_tokens":36413,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3613},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d10aae1-653c-4e0a-b24b-7a975145df68","uuid":"99a30321-10bd-4387-a641-955d71d785f2","request_id":"req_011Cc5R9A5SeU4Gz8xXkbeZF"}
