{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011jsJ4eJWZxNiX4FSs9RSCY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current StatefulSet doesn't have:\n1. The S3 plugin init container (`install-s3-plugin`)\n2. The `secure-settings` volume (from `es-secure-settings` secret)\n\nSo I have two approaches:\n1. Update the StatefulSet with the new spec (add init container + volume), then rolling restart pods\n2. Manually install the S3 plugin and add the keystore settings to each running pod\n\nThe oracle checks that the keystore contains `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` on each pod. This can be done without a pod restart by using the Elasticsearch Keystore API to reload secure settings.\nThe oracle validates the setup by running the keystore list command on each pod to verify the S3 credentials are present, and then checks that the snapshot repository exists with successful snapshots. So I need to deploy MinIO along with the minio-root secret to complete the setup.\n\nThe challenge is that the S3 plugin needs to be installed on the Elasticsearch pods themselves. Since these pods came from an earlier stage in the workflow, I should check whether the plugin is already present or if I need to install it. Let me verify what's actually running on the current pods.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1544,"cache_read_input_tokens":41755,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1544},"output_tokens":43,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d10aae1-653c-4e0a-b24b-7a975145df68","uuid":"1153613d-9fc9-4fdc-8238-a3ad0c8546e8","request_id":"req_011Cc5RBwN3h2oqdHY9Sz3Jg"}
