{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DoKHj6ByyqoWKzjRCLrCdm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is only 2 nodes right now (es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1). es-cluster-2 hasn't joined yet. Also, the curl-test pod can't reach the ES HTTP service. The cluster health is green with 2 nodes (which makes sense since we have 6 active shards = 3 primary + 3 replica but with only 2 nodes, some replicas aren't assigned... actually it says 0 unassigned shards).\n\nWait, 2 nodes with 6 active shards: that could be 3 primaries + 3 replicas distributed across 2 nodes. \n\nFor green status, all replicas must be assigned, so with 3 primaries and 3 replicas on 2 nodes, the distribution could be 3 primaries on one node and 3 replicas on the other. That's fully healthy.\n\nI'm noticing that es-cluster-0 has the old init containers (just fix-permissions and increase-vm-max-map), while es-cluster-2 has the new ones including the S3 plugin installer. So es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1 are missing the S3 plugin. I need to wait for es-cluster-2 to join the cluster first.\n\nBut there's another issue: curl-test can't reach the es-http service on port 9200, getting a connection refused error, even though es-cluster-0 can reach it locally. The problem is the service selector is looking for `app: es-cluster`, but the pods are labeled with `app: elasticsearch`, so the service isn't selecting any pods. I need to fix that selector. Patching both service selectors...\n\nBoth the `es-http` and `es-cluster` services have the wrong selector pointing to `app: es-cluster` when the actual pods are labeled with `app: elasticsearch`. This is why the headless service can't discover the pods for inter-node communication, which is likely preventing es-cluster-2 from joining the cluster. I need to correct both selectors back to `app: elasticsearch`, then monitor whether es-cluster-2 becomes ready. broke the existing cluster's services. I need to fix this right away by reverting the service selectors back to match the StatefulSet's pod labels.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":502,"cache_read_input_tokens":55081,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":502},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d10aae1-653c-4e0a-b24b-7a975145df68","uuid":"425e49ef-4741-4986-a78f-a59b594785d5","request_id":"req_011Cc5Rm7fLofe6ub7t4hkEY"}
